# Molding C8.5 Big Shift – EQMLD00147 Press 2 LEFT Shot 9

## Issue
- Molding shift: layer compound after molding offset at X-axis 0.78 mm
- Model: C8.5 Big
- Quantity: 1 panel PCB
- Machine: EQMLD00147
- Time of issue panel: 12:05 PM (07/10/2022)

## Timeline
- 08:30 AM → Big cleaning process
- 11:20 AM → Run FAI, all panel OK
- 12:20 PM → Press 2 LEFT / Shot 9: 1 panel molding shift offset found, PD stopped the machine
- 12:35 PM → EQ & ME checked all conditions to find root cause
- 13:00 PM → Machine checking finished, result normal, production continued with follow-up

## Symptom
- One panel showed molding shift offset at X-axis 0.78 mm after molding.
- The issue was found at Press 2 LEFT / Shot 9.

## Root Cause Analysis
### Verified checks
- Rechecked all PCB input:
  - Before issue: Shot 1 → 8 = normal
  - After issue: Shot 10 → 15 = normal
- Checked machine alarm log from 11:30 to 12:30:
  - machine ran normally
  - no alarm related to panel shift was recorded
- Checked CCTV from 11:30 to 12:30:
  - no operator handling abnormality
  - machine operation looked normal

### Suspected mechanism
- The NG panel may already have been abnormal before molding (examples noted in report: warpage, tape in panel, etc.)
- When the panel was pushed into moldchase, its position became incorrect (offset 0.78 mm)
- Moldchase closed while panel position was incorrect
- Pin of top mold was damaged
- Molding shift then occurred

## Failure Mechanism
- The machine, log, and CCTV review did not show clear alarm or direct handling abnormality.
- The incident was treated as a positioning-control issue linked to the panel entering moldchase in an incorrect position.
- Because the panel position exceeded the desired tolerance window, mold closing proceeded while the panel was offset.
- That incorrect closing condition likely damaged the top mold pin and created molding shift on the panel.

## Action
### Preventive action direction
Prevent issue when panel is pushed into moldchase in incorrect position.

### Setting change
- Change parameter **"Pusher small tolerance window"** from **7** to **5** in machine setting.

### Vendor / standard reference noted in report
- Based on vendor guide
- Best standard setting originally:
  - 7 ≈ 0.7 mm
- Changed to:
  - 5 ≈ 0.5 mm

### Purpose of this setting
- "Pusher small tolerance window" is used to detect panel position when the panel is pushed into the mold.
- Actual panel position must be within the tolerance window.
- If not within tolerance:
  - the press does not close
  - machine alarms
- This is intended to prevent damage to the product or the mold.

## Current Status
- Machine checking finished and machine condition was considered normal at the time of review.
- Production continued after checking.
- Follow-up is required after applying tighter pusher tolerance setting.

## Impact
- Quality: 1 panel PCB showed molding shift / offset
- Production: machine was stopped for checking, then resumed
- Safety: not stated in the report
- Repeat risk: possible if abnormal panel input condition or tolerance-window control is not sufficiently tightened

## Open Risk / Follow-up
- Need to monitor whether tighter pusher tolerance setting prevents repeat incorrect panel position
- Need to watch for recurrence of top mold pin damage
- Need to confirm if incoming abnormal panel conditions (warpage / tape / etc.) remain present

## Evidence
- Attached issue photos and timeline in report
- Before / after machine-setting screenshots for pusher small tolerance window
